40 (4) Meetings. The chairperson shall call all meetings of the committee. The committee
41 may conduct such meetings at such places and at such times as it may deem necessary or
42 convenient to enable it to exercise fully and effectively its powers, perform its duties, and
43 accomplish the objectives and purposes of this resolution.
44 (5) Allowances, expenses, and funding. The members of the committee shall receive
45 the allowances provided for in Code Section 28-1-8 of the Official Code of Georgia
46 Annotated. The allowances authorized by this resolution shall not be received by any
47 member of the committee for more than five days unless additional days are authorized.
48 Funds necessary to carry out the provisions of this resolution shall come from funds
49 appropriated to the House of Representatives.
50 (6) Report.
51 (A) In the event the committee adopts any specific findings or recommendations that
52 include suggestions for proposed legislation, the chairperson shall file a report of the
53 same prior to the date of abolishment specified in this resolution, subject to
54 subparagraph (C) of this paragraph.
55 (B) In the event the committee adopts a report that does not include suggestions for
56 proposed legislation, the chairperson shall file the report, subject to subparagraph (C)
57 of this paragraph.
58 (C) No report shall be filed unless the same has been approved prior to the date of
59 abolishment specified in this resolution by majority vote of a quorum of the committee.
60 A report so approved shall be signed by the chairperson of the committee and filed with
61 the Clerk of the House of Representatives.
62 (D) In the absence of an approved report, the chairperson may file with the Clerk of the
63 House of Representatives a copy of the minutes of the meetings of the committee in lieu
64 thereof.
65 (7) Abolishment. The committee shall stand abolished on December 1, 2025.
